The `oscrypto` library searches for the OpenSSL runtime dependency using
`ctypes.util.find_library()`, which implicitly requires a toolchain.
See:
 - https://github.com/wbond/oscrypto/blob/1.3.0/readme.md#dependencies
 - https://docs.python.org/3/library/ctypes.html#ctypes.util.find_library
 - https://docs.python.org/3/library/ctypes.html#ctypes-finding-shared-libraries

This patch hard-codes the paths to `libcrypto.so` and `libssl.so`, making
the `signapple` package self-consistent.

--- a/signapple/__init__.py
+++ b/signapple/__init__.py
@@ -1,3 +1,6 @@
+import oscrypto
+oscrypto.use_openssl(*'@GUIX_OSCRYPTO_USE_OPENSSL@'.split(','))
+
 import argparse
 
 
